package tegmentum:python-ssl@0.1.0;

/// Companion WIT for CPython's `_ssl` extension. Imports openssl:component/tls
/// (Phase 3a pivot: consume openssl-wasm's existing TLS interface directly,
/// rather than build a separate tegmentum:tls component).
///
/// The full openssl-wasm WIT (vendored under wit/deps/openssl-component/)
/// also brings in x509 and pkey, which we need for client-cert (mTLS) and
/// for building the trust store from PEM root CAs. error is brought in
/// because tls.tls-error.internal carries an error.code.
world ssl-import {
    import openssl:component/tls@0.1.0;
    import openssl:component/x509@0.1.0;
    import openssl:component/pkey@0.1.0;
    import openssl:component/error@0.1.0;
}
